<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Seizes Lebanese Forces' Assets </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Seizes Lebanese Forces' Assets </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2706190194 Beirut AL-SAFIR in Arabic 22 Jun 94 p 8 </F>
<F P=103> NC2706190194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut AL-SAFIR </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] AL-SAFIR has learned that the Lebanese State has 
seized all the Lebanese Forces' movable and immovable assets in 
Lebanon. It has obtained declarations from financial and 
administrative officials in the Lebanese Forces that they will 
not use the title deeds in their possession. The assets have 
been sold, on paper only, to these officials on direct orders 
from Samir Ja'ja'. 
  According to available information, official inquiries are 
being made to track down the Lebanese Forces' assets and 
property abroad in preparation for requesting their seizure. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

