<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hamas Leadership Reportedly Offered Base in Damascus </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hamas Leadership Reportedly Offered Base in Damascus </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2806083094 Amman AL-MAJD in Arabic 27 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN2806083094 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-MAJD </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] AL-MAJD has learned that the Syrian leadership has 
offered to host the leadership of Hamas [Islamic Resistance 
Movement] in Damascus and said it can stay for as long as it 
wants, just like other Damascus-based Palestinian opposition 
factions. 
  Informed sources said this Syrian offer was welcomed and 
appreciated by Hamas. The offer was made during meetings by 
Hamas leaders last week with a number of Syrian leaders, 
including Vice President 'Abd-al-Halim Khaddam, Foreign Minister 
Faruq al-Shar', and Sami 'Atari, member of the Ba'th Party 
National Command. 
  The sources said the Hamas delegation -- which comprised Dr. 
Musa Abu-Marzuq, head of the Hamas Political Bureau; Ibrahim 
Ghawshah, Muhammad Nazzal, and Abu-Muhammad Mustafa -- preferred 
to wait before it makes a decision until it studies the offer in 
the light of the future political developments, particularly the 
development in the Jordanian-Israeli negotiations. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

