<H3> <TI>   Minister Sees `New Forms of Protectionism' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Sees `New Forms of Protectionism' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2506125594 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0830 
GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2506125594 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] India has called upon the developing nations for 
joint action to combat new forms of protectionism. The minister 
of state for external affairs, Mr. Salman Khurshid, said 
developing countries should remain especially vigilant against 
those measures that are sought to be promoted in the guise of 
social and environmental concerns. Mr. Khurshid was addressing 
the special meeting of G-77 [Group of 77] developing nations in 
New York yesterday. He said it is important for the developing 
countries to ensure that their major trading partners in the 
industrial world observe the rule of law and of free trade and 
competition. 

</TEXT>

