  [Text] The Jerusalem City Council decided on a series of 
measures to prevent Yasir 'Arafat's visit in the city. In a 
special session held this morning, the mayor and all his eight 
deputies decided to set up three action committees: a public 
relations committee, a financial committee, and a committee 
which would organize a huge protest campaign. Our correspondent 
Aviv Bushinsky reports that, among other things, the Jerusalem 
City Council plans to fly in protesters from overseas aboard 
special planes. 

