<H3> <TI>   Baraq: IDF To Implement Shamgar Recommendations Fully </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Baraq: IDF To Implement Shamgar Recommendations Fully </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2806045094 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0400 GMT 28 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2806045094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Speaking at a General Staff forum on the Shamgar 
Commission's recommendations, the chief of staff said the IDF 
[Israel Defense Forces] will make preparations to implement the 
commission's conclusions speedily and fully. 
  Our army affairs correspondent Karmela Menashe notes that in 
the wake of the commission's criticism, the IDF will soon issue 
orders and clarifications concerning the use of gunfire against 
settlers and violations of law and order in the territories by 
Jews. 
  The Cave of the Patriarchs will open only when all the 
security arrangements are in place and the complete separation 
of Jews and Arabs is assured. The IDF will maintain a guard 
force at the cave and bar armed worshipers from the site. IDF 
sources stress that Army elements had cautioned already last 
year that the law was not being enforced against settlers and 
had requested police reinforcements at the site. IDF elements 
stress that procedures for cooperation between the army and the 
police are of vital importance at this time. 

</TEXT>

