<H3> <TI>   Opening Ties With Tunisia `Next Month' Discussed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Opening Ties With Tunisia `Next Month' Discussed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2306180894 Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Hebrew 1700 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2306180894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Hebrew 1700 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Israel and Tunisia are discussing a possibile 
opening of representation offices next month, for the first 
time. Our correspondent Gadi Sukenik reports that Deputy 
Foreign Minister Yosi Beilin left for Paris this morning for a 
working visit, in the course of which he will meet with the top 
echelons of the French Foreign Ministry. Among other things, he 
will try to promote the Israel-Tunisia relations. In some two 
weeks, Beilin will travel to Tunisia as head of the Israeli 
delegation for the steering committee of the multilateral peace 
talks. In his meetings with top Tunisian officials, he will 
attempt to conclude the establishment of relations, perhaps a 
mutual opening of interest offices. 

</TEXT>

