<H3> <TI>   Reports on Incidents of Violence Continue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reports on Incidents of Violence Continue </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Arab Shot Dead in Nabulus </H4>

<F P=102> TA2406163394 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1600 GMT 24 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2406163394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] An Arab youth was shot and killed during a riot in 
Nabulus at noon following a demonstration demanding the release 
of all Palestinian prisoners. Our correspondent Moti Amir 
reports that there were similar demonstrations in other towns in 
the territories, and in Gaza and Jericho in the autonomy. 
  In Gaza, thousands today attended the funeral of Hamas 
[Islamic Resistance Movement] activist Nasir Faluha, who was 
murdered yesterday. The Palestinian police safeguarded the 
funeral procession. During the funeral ceremony there were 
calls to kill Faluha's murderer. Our correspondent Nisim Qeynan 
notes that the Palestinian police detained a suspect, 
'Abd-al-Salam 'Alwan, a brother of a collaborator murdered 
several months ago by Hamas' 'Izz-al-Din al-Qassam military arm. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-38068 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes124_l_94019" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-124 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  26 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reports on Incidents of Violence Continue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reports on Incidents of Violence Continue </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Palestinian Suspect in Tel Aviv Murder </H4>

<F P=102> TA2606153394 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1500 GMT 26 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2606153394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] David Mishli, a 30-year-old resident of Tel Aviv, 
was killed, apparently with an iron bar, in his launderette in 
the Shapira neighborhood today. Police say their main suspect 
is Sa'idi Khalil Jabr, a Palestinian who cooperated with Israeli 
authorities and was given permission to live in the south Tel 
Aviv neighborhood. They say he had announced he would do 
something to return to the ranks of the Fatah organization. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

