<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reports on Incidents of Violence Continue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reports on Incidents of Violence Continue </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Arab Reportedly Stabs Jew in Jerusalem </H4>

<F P=102> TA2806084594 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0800 GMT 28 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2806084594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A young Jew was stabbed in the head in Jerusalem's 
Neve Ya'aqov neighborhood this morning, and his condition is 
very serious. Our correspondent Aviv Bushinsky reports that the 
man was repairing his car when he was suddenly stabbed by a 
young Arab wielding a large knife. He was sent to Hadassah-'En 
Kerem Hospital with head and neck injuries. The knife was found 
near the scene, but the Arab assailant had fled to the village 
of Dahiyat al-Barid. 
  The police have his description. He is believed to have been 
employed as a laborer in the Neve Ya'aqov neighborhood. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

