<H3> <TI>   Envoy to Sweden Denies Intention To Resign </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Envoy to Sweden Denies Intention To Resign </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2706180794 Stockholm Radio Sweden in English 1615 GMT 27 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2706180794 </F>
<F P=104>  Stockholm Radio Sweden </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Sudanese ambassador to Stockholm has disputed 
claims that he has resigned and asked for political asylum in 
Sweden. Sources in the Sudanese capital claimed over the weekend 
that Mohammad Zein left his post after the Sudanese Government 
recalled him to Khartoum, but the ambassador said today he had 
no intention of resigning. Sudanese sources said Mr. Zein had 
held office under the former government of Sadeq al-Mahdi, who 
was arrested last week on conspiracy charges. 

</TEXT>

