<H3> <TI>   Statement Issued on Talks With Yemeni Delegation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Statement Issued on Talks With Yemeni Delegation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2706223694 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 2200 
GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2706223694 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Affairs Minister Mohamed Salah Dembri 
received today the Yemeni parliamentary delegation led by Mr. 
'Abd al-Wahab Mahmud, deputy speaker of the parliament and 
chairman of the Foreign Affairs Committee. The delegation is 
visiting Algeria in the framework of a mission aimed at 
informing and consulting with the Transitional National Council. 
  A Foreign Ministry statement said that the talks dealt with 
the latest developments in Yemen. In this respect, the Yemeni 
delegation gave the parliament's view on the fratricidal 
fighting that is tearing the country apart. The delegation also 
expressed the parliament's desire to use every means to achieve 
a settlement of the conflict with the help of sister and 
friendly countries. 
  The statement added that Mr. Dembri had insisted on the 
pressing need for the warring sides to stop the fighting in 
order to provide the minimum conditions for the resumption of 
the dialogue and open the way to a peaceful settlement of the 
conflict. In this context, the minister affirmed Algeria's 
readiness to contribute to the efforts aimed at ending the 
conflict between the brothers in Yemen. 

</TEXT>

