<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Algeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Trial of Boudiaf Assassin Set for Jul </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Trial of Boudiaf Assassin Set for Jul </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2706212694 Algiers ENTV Television Network in Arabic 1900 
GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2706212694 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers ENTV Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The court of criminal appeal of Algiers Judicial 
Council today issued a ruling in the case of the deceased 
president, Mohamed Boudiaf, and decided to refer the defendant 
Boumaarafi Lembarek to the criminal court of Algiers Judicial 
Council. Boumaarafi is charged with committing a premeditated 
murder, causing deliberate injuries with firearms, and planning 
to topple the regime. These crimes are punishable in accordance 
with Articles 254, 255, 261, 256, 257, 77, and 266 of the penal 
code. 
  It is worth noting that the court of criminal appeal had, on 
1 March 1994, ruled in favor of further investigations into the 
case to examine all the elements of the inquiry. Afterwards the 
measures linked to these additional inquiries were implemented 
by the examining magistrate who was busy completing the 
investigation entrusted to him. At the end of his mission, the 
magistrate sent the file back to the court of criminal appeal of 
Algiers Judicial Council which, after examining it, ruled to 
refer the defendant Boumaarafi Lembarek to the criminal court of 
Algiers Judicial Council. Thus, the case is now ready to be 
examined at a trial. The trial is due to start in July 1994, in 
accordance with the provisions of the law. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-38078 </DOCNO>
