<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Afghanistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Seen Making Progress Against Militia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Seen Making Progress Against Militia </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Dostam Aircraft Bomb Herat </H4>

<F P=102> LD2606171794 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network in Pashto 1530 
GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2606171794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Pashto </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Approximately 100 people were killed or injured 
yesterday during an air attack against Herat city. 
  A Bakhtar Information Agency correspondent reports from 
Herat 
city that two jets belonging to Dostam's militia bombed the 
crowded parts of Herat city yesterday. As a result, eight 
civilians were killed and around 90 people--including women and 
children--were injured. 
  The report adds that this savage attack occurred on the eve 
of a meeting of the country's governors in Herat and was an 
attempt to undermine this meeting. It was reported that the 
meeting is scheduled to be held in two days--on 28 June. In 
addition to the country's governors, a number of social and 
scientific personalities from in and out of Afghanistan will 
attend it. It is expected that a number of leaders of the 
jihadi groups will also participate. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

