<H4>    Latest Fighting Leaves 35 Dead </H4>

<F P=102> BK2806013294 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 0100 
GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2806013294 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Urdu </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to reports, fierce fighting continues in 
southeast Afghanistan. A spokesman of Prime Minister Golboddin 
Hekmatyar has claimed that the combined forces of Hekmatyar and 
General Abdol Rashid Dostam have reoccupied one out of two 
strategic positions in the country's southern region. 
Independent sources, however, have not confirmed this claim. 
The reports say at least 35 people have been killed and 360 
others injured in the latest flare up of fighting. 
  Meanwhile, a meeting of the jehad leaders assessed the 
current situation in Afghanistan. A joint statement issued 
after the meeting calls for an urgent meeting of the Leadership 
Council to decide on the future government as the term of office 
of President Borhanoddin Rabbani and Prime Minister Golboddin 
Hekmatyar expires today. Among those who attended the meeting 
include former president Professor Mojadeddi, Shaykh Asef 
Mohseni, Pir Seyyed Ahmad Gilani, and Maulvi Mohammad Nabi 
Mohammadi. 

</TEXT>

