<H4>    Missiles Kill 13 in Kabul </H4>

<F P=102> LD2806102694 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2806102694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In line with the continuation of fighting among the 
involved sides in the capital of Afghanistan, Kabul city center 
was this morning subjected to strikes by dozens of missiles. 
According to a report by the Central News Desk from Kabul, the 
missiles landed on central parts of Kabul city and caused 
considerable damage, leaving at least 13 people dead and a large 
number wounded. The hospital sources in Kabul likewise 
announced that in the course of the past three days' fighting in 
Kabul 100 people were killed and 500 were injured. 
  A report by AFP states that a spokesman for the UN secretary 
general has announced: Within the framework of revival of the 
political presence of this organization in Afghanistan, a 
special team will visit this country. He added: Until the 
security situation improves in Kabul, the UN mission will be 
established temporarily in Jalalabad. 

</TEXT>

