<H3> <TI>   Investigation of Mashhad Bombing Continues </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Investigation of Mashhad Bombing Continues </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    National Security Council Meets </H4>

<F P=102> LD2506171994 Tehran IRIB Television Second Program Network 
in Persian 1600 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2506171994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRIB Television Second Program Network 
in Persian 1600 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The country's Supreme National Security Council met 
this evening and stressed the importance of law enforcement 
officials continuing their activities toward achieving the 
quickest possible identification and capture of the criminals 
behind the heart-rending incident at the blessed shrine of Imam 
Reza -- peace be upon Him -- in keeping with the guidance issued 
by the eminent leader. 
  The session was attended by President Hashemi-Rafsanjani and 
by members and high-ranking military commanders. The various 
dimensions of the recent horrific crime committed by the 
Mojahedin-e Khalq Organization at the blessed shrine of the 
eighth imam -- peace be upon Him -- were examined, and law 
enforcement and security officials briefed the council members 
in this regard. 
  The council praised the efforts made by security officials 
and stressed the importance of pursuing and intensifying these 
efforts. 

</TEXT>

