<H4>    Khamene'i Criticizes Rights Groups </H4>

<F P=102> LD2706155694 Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network in 
Persian 1430 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2706155694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] During a speech at a meeting this morning with 
judiciary officials and judges from all over the country, His 
Eminence Ayatollah Khamene'i, the great leader of the Islamic 
revolution, stressed the importance of discipline and stability 
in the judiciary. [passage omitted] 
  Criticizing those organizations that advocate human rights, 
His Eminence Ayatollah Khamene'i said: Those who burned alive 
dozens of people last year and followed an overt racist policy 
in their countries do not have the right to utter the words 
human rights from their filthy mouths and expect the observance 
of human rights from others. 
  The leader of the Islamic revolution admonished the world 
forums and committees that advocate human rights for their 
silence regarding one of the greatest terrorist tragedies. He 
said: Those so-called human rights committees and forums, which 
have brought politics into everything, have turned a blind eye 
to that great terrorist tragedy at the shrine of Imam 
Reza--peace be upon him--and have not said a word about it. 
Those who are constantly saying that the greatest threat to the 
world today is terrorism have kept silent about the 'Ashura 
tragedy in Mashhad. Therefore, what right do they have to 
meddle in matters relating to the observance of human rights in 
other countries. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

