<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Amphibious Exercise Successfully Concluded </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Amphibious Exercise Successfully Concluded </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2306103294 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2306103294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The amphibious Zafar-1 joint military exercise, 
which started in Persian Gulf waters and the strategic Strait of 
Hormoz on 30 Khordad [20 June], was concluded successfully today. 
  Light and heavy vessels, fast assault boats, rangers, and 
commandoes of the Armed Forces and the Islamic Revolution Guard 
Corps, and a number of fighter-bombers of the Islamic Republic 
Air Force took part in the exercise. 
  Operations were carried out in six phases, involving the 
control of communication routes and navy equipment; dispatching 
units of light vessels; air and surface bombardment of 
communication routes, vital positions, and installations of an 
imaginary enemy; reconnaissance and mine-sweeping operations by 
special teams; and capturing the positions and sea rescue 
operations of the vessels of the imaginary enemy. 
  The Zafar-1 maneuver is one of a series of joint annual 
exercises of the Armed Forces and the Guards Corps, aimed at 
raising defensive capabilities and exchanging experience and 
military know-how. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

