<F P=100> Libya </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Qadhdhafi Comments on Lockerbie, al-Kikhya </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Qadhdhafi Comments on Lockerbie, al-Kikhya </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2706135994 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1335 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2706135994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Sirte, 27 June (MENA) -- [passage omitted] 
Al-Qadhdhafi said that the recent proposal adopted by the Arab 
League on the Lockerbie case could be the only solution for this 
crisis. He added that this proposal, which "is convincing and 
satisfactory for all the parties," will be submitted to the 
Security Council by the Arab group, the nonaligned countries, 
and the African states and could be accepted because it is not a 
Libyan one. 
  In his remarks on developments in the Lockerbie case, Col. 
al-Qadhdhafi said that there are now strong suspicions that 
Libya is not the sole defendant in this case but that there are 
several parties, especially after the confessions of Yusuf 
Sha'ban, who is being tried before a Lebanese court. 
  On tightening the sanctions imposed on Libya, he stressed 
that his country is ready to confront any situation. But he 
expressed his belief that the European countries will be the 
only losers in this. 
  On his meeting with the wife of Mansur al-Kikhya [Libyan 
dissident who disappeared while in Egypt], al-Qadhdhafi said: 
We met and I stressed to her that the security organs in Egypt 
and Libya are fully cooperating to uncover the truth. He 
pointed a finger of accusation at the U.S. intelligence and its 
Libyan agents. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

