<H3> <TI>   Al-Baz on Possible Solution to Lockerbie Issue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Baz on Possible Solution to Lockerbie Issue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2706140694 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1350 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2706140694 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sirte, 27 Jun (MENA)-- Dr. Usamah al-Baz, first 
Foreign Ministry under secretary and director of the President's 
Office for Political Affairs, expressed his belief that a 
solution could be reached on the Lockerbie problem between Libya 
and the Western countries. 
  In a statement he made before leaving Sirte with the 
delegation accompanying President Husni Mubarak, al-Baz said 
that a number of proposals on this issue were discussed during 
the meetings held by the Egyptian and Libyan sides. He stressed 
that a solution that upholds the two sides' sovereignty can be 
reached. 
  He added that it was agreed to have the higher 
Egyptian-Libyan committee chaired by the two countries' prime 
ministers meet in Cairo during the first week of August and its 
meeting will be preceded by a meeting of the preparatory 
committee. 

</TEXT>

