<H3> <TI>   Fighting Between Opposition, Regime Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fighting Between Opposition, Regime Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2706174494 (Clandestine) Voice of the People of Kurdistan 
in Arabic 1600 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2706174494 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of the People of Kurdistan 
in Arabic 1600 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The newspaper KURDISTAN NWAY, in today's issue, 
quoted exclusive sources as saying that clashes have taken place 
between the Iraqi opposition forces and the regime's forces in 
and around Baghdad and in Iraq's southern areas. The regime's 
troops sustained casualties as a result. The paper noted that a 
fierce clash took place at midnight on 9 June in al-Thawrah city 
between a unit from the Iraqi opposition and security forces 
from the Baghdad regime. Various types of weapons were used in 
the clash, which lasted for approximately 30 minutes. Two 
policemen were killed as a result. 
  On 11 June, a violent battle took place on the main road 
between al-Khalis and (al-Ba'kumah) cities. The battle later 
spread to the nearby fields [words indistinct]. The dictatorial 
regime used large-caliber weapons to shell the areas surrounding 
al-Khalis. Sounds of artillery shelling were heard in the [name 
indistinct]. A destroyed vehicle was seen on the main road and 
three bodies were found inside it. The paper added that 
extensive battles between Iraqi opposition and regime troops 
took place in the al-Salam and al-Maymuna marshes of al-'Amarah 
Governorate on 11 June. The dictatorial forces sustained severe 
casualties. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

