<H3> <TI>   UN Informed of U-2 Plane Violations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UN Informed of U-2 Plane Violations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2806104194 Baghdad INA in English 0850 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2806104194 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] New York, June 28, INA -- Iraq has protested to the 
United Nations over continued violation of its airspace by the 
U-2 spy aircraft under pretext of carrying out aerial survey for 
the UN Special Commission. 
  In a message to UN Chief Dr Butrus Ghali, Foreign Minister 
Muhammad Sa'id al-Sahhaf said that the U-2 spy aircraft violated 
the Iraqi airspace four times over May 30 ending June 23. 
[sentence as received] 
  The minister said that this aircraft is used for purposes 
contrary to those underlined by the Security Council and its 
activities prejudice Iraq's sovereignty and security and 
intercept goals and principles of the United Nations in 
respecting equity and sovereignty of all member states. 
  He called upon the United Nations to immediately reconsider 
the use of this aircraft. 

</TEXT>

