<H3> <TI>   Transportation Agreement Signed With Sudan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Transportation Agreement Signed With Sudan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA2606125894 Khartoum SUNA in Arabic 1600 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> EA2606125894 </F>
<F P=104>  Khartoum SUNA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Khartoum, 26 June (SUNA) -- A technical cooperation 
agreement in the field of transportation has been signed between 
Sudan and Iraq. The agreement deals with ports, civil aviation, 
railways, land and sea transport, and the exchange of skills and 
technical training in these fields. 
  The agreement was signed in Baghdad yesterday by 
Transportation Minister 'Uthman 'Abd-al-Qadir 'Abd al-Latif, who 
is visiting Iraq. Dr. Ahmad Murtada Ahmad Khalil, Iraq's 
minister of transport and communication, signed on behalf of his 
country. 
  After the signing, 'Uthman 'Abd-al-Qadir 'Abd al-Latif 
reiterated that Sudan stands alongside Iraq in its confrontation 
with imperialism and Zionism, which target the Arab nation. He 
praised the support that Iraq continues to extend to Sudan in 
different fields, especially in the field of transportation. 
  The Iraqi minister stressed that his country was eager to 
develop its relations with Sudan, provide it with technical 
skills, and benefit from Sudanese skills in return. He said all 
the Iraqi ministry's technical institutions and facilities are 
fully ready to provide training opportunities to the Sudanese. 

</TEXT>

