Arabic 1030 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2706120094 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ahmad Shakir, president of the Society for the 
Advancement of Arab-French Relations, today arrived in Baghdad 
leading a delegation on a visit of several days to Iraq. 
  In a statement to the IRAQI NEWS AGENCY, Shakir said the 
purpose of his visit is to hold talks with Iraqi officials on 
the prospects for cooperation between Iraq and France in all 
fields and means to promote this cooperation. 
  He added that during the visit, the delegation will study 
the 
effects of the continued embargo and the Iraqi people's 
suffering as a result of the acute shortage in food, medicine, 
and other essential supplies. 
  He stressed that the French people have began to understand 
the Iraqi people's suffering as a result of the blockade. 
  The delegation comprises Senator (Jean Jacques), deputy 
chairman of the French Senate's Iraq-France Relations Committee, 
and a number of French businessmen. 

</TEXT>

