  [Text] Baghdad, 27 Jun (INA)--Dr. 'Abd-al-Razzaq 
al-Hashimi, head of the Foreign Relations Bureau at the Iraq 
Command of the Arab Socialist Ba'th Party and chairman of the 
Iraqi-French Friendship Society, met here today with Ahmad 
Shakir, chairman of the Association for Developing Arab-French 
Relations, and his delegation. 
  During the meeting, Dr. 'Abd-al-Razzaq al-Hashimi reviewed 
the impact of the unfair embargo clamped on Iraq, affirming that 
there is no longer any justification for maintaining this 
embargo, particularly since Iraq has fulfilled its commitments 
per the relevant UN Security Council resolutions. 
  Al-Hashimi also underscored the importance of promoting and 
normalizing trade and economic ties between Iraq and France in 
the interest of the two countries' peoples. 
  For his part, the chairman of the Association for Developing 
Arab-French Relations expressed his willingness to continue to 
work for the lifting of the unfair sanctions imposed on the 
people of Iraq. 
  A delegation from the association arrived in Baghdad earlier 
today. The delegation comprises French Senate Member Jean 
Jacques Robier and representatives of several French firms and 
banks. 

