<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<H3> <TI>   GCC Foreign Ministers Meet on Peace Preparation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    GCC Foreign Ministers Meet on Peace Preparation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2506185594 Kuwait KUNA in Arabic 1720 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2506185594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuwait KUNA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Riyad, 25 Jun -- A meeting of representatives of 
foreign ministers of the Gulf Cooperation Council [GCC] in 
Riyadh today to prepare for the next meeting of the 
international steering committee set up to work in tandem with 
the Israeli-Arab peace talks. 
  The committee includes members of a joint 
Palestinian-Jordanian delegation; and representatives of Israel, 
Saudi Arabia -- representing the GCC states --Tunisia, Egypt, 
Canada, Japan, and the European Union, in addition to 
representatives of Russia and the United States as co-sponsors 
of the peace process. 
  Diplomatic sources in Riyadh told KUNA that the Gulf 
officials will discuss the statement of principles to be 
submitted to the steering committee, which defines the agenda of 
talks on arms control in the Middle East and regional security 
in the future. 
  The sources added that the committee, which oversees the 
work 
of other committees emanates from the multilateral talks, will 
also discuss the resolutions issued by the arms control 
committee at the end of its meeting held in Qatar last April. 
  At its last meeting, the international steering committee 
discussed the results of meetings of the working groups set up 
in Moscow in January 1993. The groups dealt with issues of arms 
control, refugees, economic cooperation, water resources, and 
environment. 

</TEXT>

