<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister al-Shar' Receives Iranian Envoy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Minister al-Shar' Receives Iranian Envoy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2706090294 Tehran IRNA in English 0817 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2706090294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Damascus, June 27, IRNA -- The Iranian ambassador to 
Damascus, Mohammad Hassan Akhtari, here Sunday called on the 
Syrian Foreign Minister Faruq al-Shar' and discussed bilateral 
issues and the current developments in the region. 
  Expressing his condolences over the martyrdom of scores of 
pilgrims in the holy shrine of Imam Reza in Mashhad, Al-Shar' 
condemned the savage act of bomb blast by the terrorist 
Mojahedin-e Khalq Organization (MKO). 
  Referring to friendly relations between the two countries, 
the Syrian foreign minister voiced his country's support for 
Iran's stances in all domains. 

</TEXT>

