<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mubarak Returns From Libya Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mubarak Returns From Libya Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2706165994 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1605 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2706165994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 27 Jun (MENA)--President Husni Mubarak 
returned to Cairo this afternoon following a two-day visit to 
the Libyan al-Jamahiriyah, during which he held intensive talks 
with Libyan revolution leader Brother Colonel Mu'ammar 
al-Qadhdhafi that dealt with the Libyan-Western crisis, 
"Lockerbie," and Egypt's efforts to find a solution to it. 
  The two leaders' talks also focused on developments in the 
Yemeni crisis, the Middle East peace talks developments, and the 
situation on all the tracks of the Arab-Israeli negotiations. 
The talks also dealt with developments in Africa, the outcome 
of the recent OAU summit in Tunis, and the consultations held by 
the African leaders on the summit sidelines. 
  The Egyptian and Libyan delegations also discussed bilateral 
relations and assessed their views of the decisions already made 
by the higher Egyptian-Libyan committee. The two sides 
discussed within this context the implementation of the project 
to extend by 170 kms the railroad between Musa'id and Tubruq. 
  The official delegation that accompanied the president 
during 
the visit returned with him. 

</TEXT>

