<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   PUK, KDP Leaders Agree To Resolve Problems </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PUK, KDP Leaders Agree To Resolve Problems </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2706181594 (Clandestine) Voice of the People of Kurdistan 
in Arabic 1600 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2706181594 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of the People of Kurdistan 
in Arabic 1600 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A meeting was held in Irbil today between officials 
from the Patriotic Union of Kurdistan [PUK] and the Kurdistan 
Democratic Party [KDP] in the presence of a delegation from 
Socialist International. Party leader Mas'ud Barzani, Dr. Rawj 
Nuri Shawij, and [names indistinct] attended the meeting from 
the KDP. From the PUK the meeting was attended by leader Jalal 
Talabani, Kusret Rasul 'Ali, and [names indistinct]. 
  During a bilateral meeting held between brother Talabani and 
Barzani, an agreement was reached to invite the political 
bureaus of the PUK and KDP to a meeting tomorrow, call on the 
government and the parliament to immediately assume their 
customary duties, and suspend media campaigns. An agreement was 
also reached on the need for the two political bureaus to 
prepare the necessary plans to tackle all the problems between 
the two sides and invite the leaders of the Kurdistan Front to 
the same meeting to help resolve these problems. 

</TEXT>

