<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Masri Assesses King's Trip, Negotiations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Masri Assesses King's Trip, Negotiations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2706134894 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1100 GMT 
27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2706134894 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] House of Representatives Speaker Tahir al-Masri 
has stated that His Majesty King Husayn's recent visit to 
Washington constitutes one of his majesty's most important 
visits abroad in terms of timing, content, and results both in 
the local and regional arenas. [passage omitted] 
  In a statement to the Jordanian News Agency, al-Masri added 
that his majesty believes that cohesion on the internal front, 
overcoming economic difficulties, and promoting Jordan's 
democratic, economic, and development march cannot be ignored in 
any political move and that Israel's recognition of Jordan's 
sovereignty over its usurped territories, as well as returning 
its full water rights, will be useful for our Arab brothers in 
their negotiations on the other tracks. If the Arab rights are 
recognized on their tracks--a matter that has taken place on the 
Jordanian track--then this principle would apply to other tracks 
and all aspects of Arab rights. 
  He also said that the House of Representatives always 
supports any accomplishment and policy that enables Jordan to 
restore its rights, promote its development, and achieve the 
utmost Arab coordination with the other Arab brothers in order 
to reach a concerted comprehensive solution. 
  Al-Masri added: I understand the extent of doubts and fears 
of many of the sons of our people, but stagnation and the lack 
of movement in the international arena, as well as allowing 
fears and points of weakness to overwhelm confidence and the 
points of strength in the Arab Islamic society in Jordan and 
abroad, will only lead to more Zionist control of the region and 
the international circles. Jordan's move toward negotiations 
and peace issues, he added, has not come in a vacuum, has not 
been hasty, and will, with God's help and King Husayn's wisdom, 
pursue this course to achieve the goals in which our loyal 
Jordanians believe and for which they are working. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

