<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   First Commercial Strike Announced in Jericho </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    First Commercial Strike Announced in Jericho </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2706174094 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 1600 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2706174094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv IDF Radio </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A general commercial strike was announced in 
Jericho today, and most of the city's stores remained closed. 
The strike was called to protest the continued incarceration of 
Palestinians in Israeli prisons. The Jericho strike is the 
first since the IDF [Israel Defense Forces] handed over the area 
to the Palestinian police. 
  Also today, Jericho was re-opened to tourists. 

</TEXT>

