<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Aloni Says Sha'th To Visit Jerusalem </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Aloni Says Sha'th To Visit Jerusalem </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2906053494 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0500 GMT 29 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2906053494 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Nabil Sha'th will come to Jerusalem on 1 July and 
will watch a joint Palestinian-Israeli theater production. 
According to Minister Shulamit Aloni, the prime minister 
approved the visit. 
  At the same time, Jerusalem Mayor Ehud Olmert said this 
morning that this is not about a theater performance; rather, 
the Sha'th visit is a political demonstration by the PLO, and he 
will have no part of it. Minister Aloni said that at this 
stage, Jerusalem is a religious issue and that there is nothing 
more wonderful than having the capital of the Jewish people open 
to all. 
  Olmert said he is pleased that in his meeting with the prime 
minister yesterday they did not deal with philosophy, because 
the issues at hand are political. The Jerusalem mayor said he 
is pleased with what he heard from the prime minister, but added 
that he gives Mr. Rabin and the government six months to prove 
their intentions in deeds, such as allocating resources for the 
city, expanding construction there, building roads, and 
developing the education system in both parts of the city. 
  Aloni and Olmert spoke to Qol Yisra'el this morning. 

</TEXT>

