<F P=102>   LD2806131194 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Overseas Service in 
English 1100 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2806131194 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Overseas Service </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pakistan has urged President Borhanoddin Rabbani, 
Prime Minister Golboddin Hekmatyar, and other leaders of 
Afghanistan to stop fighting and sit together to resolve their 
differences. The call was made by the foreign minister, Ali 
Sardar Asif Ahmad, while talking to newsmen in Islamabad today. 
He also called upon the Afghan leaders to accept any invitation 
to them by the ICO [Islamic Conference Organization] to discuss 
a draft peace plan. 
  Meanwhile in the Afghan capital, Kabul, jet fighters of the 
forces opposed to President Borhanoddin Rabbani bombed the 
center of the city for the second day today, killing 12 people 
and injuring several others. 

</TEXT>

