<H3> <TI>   Ba'th Party Delegation Leaves for Jordan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ba'th Party Delegation Leaves for Jordan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2806114994 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in 
Arabic 1030 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2806114994 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Comrade 'Abd-al-Ghani 'Abd-al-Ghafur, member of the 
Iraq Command of the Arab Socialist Ba'th Party, and his 
delegation today left for Amman on a visit of several days to 
Jordan at the invitation of Jordanian political forces and 
organizations. 
  Comrade 'Abd-al-Ghani 'Abd-al-Ghafur told an Iraqi News 
Agency correspondent that the Arab Socialist Ba'th Party 
delegation will hold meetings with political parties and forces 
in fraternal Jordan to activate the joint pan-Arab action in an 
effort to employ all means to lift the unjust blockade imposed 
on Iraq, which fulfilled all of its obligations toward the UN 
Security Council resolutions despite the injustice and 
unfairness it had to endure. 
  He said the serious departure from the biased U.S. stand by 
some UN Security Council permanent members and other members 
during the previous two reviews in March and May puts on the 
political parties and forces, the Arab nation's masses, and the 
virtuous people of the world a responsibility to continue the 
work to lift the unjust blockade imposed on Iraq through party 
and parliamentary activities before the next UN Security Council 
review in July. 
  The Arab Socialist Ba'th Party delegation includes comrades 
'Abd-al-Razzaq al-Hashimi, head of the Foreign Relations Bureau, 
and Sa'd Qasim Hammudi, member of the Foreign Relations Bureau. 

</TEXT>

