BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, 28 Jun (INA) -- Trade Minister Dr. 
Muhammad Mahdi Salih has met with Ahmad Shakir, head of the 
society for promoting Arab-French relations, and his 
accompanying delegation. 
  During the meeting, the minister reviewed the repercussions 
of the continued criminal, unfair economic blockade imposed on 
the Iraqi people in violation of international and humanitarian 
laws and norms, as well as the Iraqi people's suffering due to 
the severe shortage of food and medications. 
  The French delegation expressed its appreciation for the 
construction achieved in Iraq, which was based on its own 
capabilities despite the blockade imposed on it. The delegation 
also said that it hoped the blockade will be lifted as soon as 
possible and that French-Iraqi relations will return to normal 
in order to serve the interests of both countries. 

