<F P=100> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister Departs on Visit to Russia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prime Minister Departs on Visit to Russia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2906091294 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0830 
GMT 29 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2906091294 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The prime minister left New Delhi this afternoon for 
Moscow on a four-day official visit. Mr. Narasimha Rao was seen 
off at the Delhi airport by several union ministers, the three 
service chiefs, and senior officials, among others. Mr. Rao is 
heading a high-level delegation and will have wide-ranging talks 
with the Russian president, Mr. Yeltsin, and other leaders. 
  Our correspondent, Kajal Das, accompanying the prime 
minister, reports that bilateral trade which witnessed a slump 
in recent years will get a boost from this visit. Russia has 
already offered to set up joint ventures out of the Rupee-Ruble 
Repayment Fund. The high-level delegation accompanying Mr. 
Narasima Rao includes union ministers Mr. Pranab Mukherjee, Mr. 
Ghulam Nabi Azad, Mr. R.L. Bhatia, and Mr. Bhubanesh Chaturvedi, 
and defense and foreign secretaries. 

</TEXT>

