<H3> <TI>   Ministry Denies Holding Israeli Pilot </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry Denies Holding Israeli Pilot </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2906055594 Tehran IRNA in English 0548 GMT 29 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2906055594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, June 29, IRNA -- Iran's foreign Ministry 
Tuesday [28 June] categorically denied allegations made by the 
Zionist regime on the presence of an Israeli pilot in Iran and 
termed it as "sheer lie". 
  Israeli Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin and the Zionist 
regime's 
Air Force commander recently had claimed that Ron Arad, an 
Israeli pilot whose plane crashed in 1986 while bombarding south 
Lebanon, is in Iran. 
  An informed source at the Foreign Ministry in a contact with 
IRNA categorically rejected the allegations and stressed "the 
Zionists were following other objectives by repeating such 
baseless and unfounded claims." 

</TEXT>

