<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official: UAE's Claim to Islands `Baseless' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official: UAE's Claim to Islands `Baseless' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2806175494 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1630 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2806175494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Following recent remarks by Shaykh Hamdan, the UAE's 
minister of state for foreign affairs, which once again 
reiterated that country's baseless claims, the spokesman of our 
country's Foreign Affairs Ministry has stressed Iran's 
sovereignty over the three Iranian islands [in the Gulf]. 
  Mr Mohammadi said: Repeating such baseless issues, which 
undermine the process of consolidation of stability in the 
region, serves only the interests of foreigners and helps the 
Zionist regime spread its influence in the region. 
  He added: Expansion of ties and cooperation does not mean 
serving one-sided interests. Instead, such a process embraces 
the mutual interests of the two neighboring Muslim countries, 
and in the opinion of the Islamic Republic of Iran, expansion of 
ties requires that one should refrain from making territorial 
claims, and should instead pay respect to the issues of 
sovereignty and established frontiers. 
  Furthermore, he stressed: Instead of attention to propaganda 
issues, it is better for the UAE to accept the Islamic Republic 
of Iran's invitation to hold bilateral talks. 

</TEXT>

