Daily Report 
<DATE1>  29 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Presidents Preview Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Presidents Preview Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2906104694 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 29 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2906104694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] President Geydar Aliyev of Azerbaijan arrived in 
Tehran this morning at the head of a high-ranking political, 
economic, social, and cultural delegation. He was formally 
welcomed by President Hashemi-Rafsanjani. 
  After arriving in Tehran Mr. Aliyev, in an interview with 
our 
correspondent, referred to the Islamic Republic of Iran [IRI] 
and our country's revolutionary people as the friends and 
sincere brothers of the Azerbaijan Republic. Referring to the 
two countries' common historical, national, and religious 
background, he said: We attach great importance to the IRI as an 
influential and powerful neighbor and we would like the two 
countries to expand ties in all fields. The president of 
Azerbaijan added that during his stay in our country he will 
hold talks with President Hashemi-Rafsanjani and other IRI 
officials on the most significant regional and international 
issues and the expansion of the two countries' relations. 
  On the axes of talks with Azerbaijan's president and the two 
countries' ties, Mr. Hashemi-Rafsanjani said: 
  [Begin Hashemi-Rafsanjani recording] In the name of God, the 
compassionate, the merciful. We are very close to Azerbaijan in 
every respect. Our people feel solidarity [yeganegi] in both 
countries. At present the level of our ties is very good too. 
During my visit to Baku -- frankly -- among the authorities, 
with Mr. Aliyev himself, and among the people I felt as if they 
were like our own people. Fortunately many of the decisions we 
took during that visit are currently being implemented. Of 
course some of the important decisions require time for 
implementation. We have had some memoranda of understanding, 
which we will pursue during this visit. 
  To us the problem of military conflict in Caucasia is highly 
significant. One of the subjects of our talks, therefore, will 
be the same issues of Karabakh and the problems of Caucasia in 
general. 
  Among our important issues are cooperation in the Caspian 
Sea 
and greater utilization of the joint river of Aras. There are 
the issues of transit, trade and exchange visits by our people. 
Almost all the issues that the two countries are interested in 
and eager to discuss will be discussed during this visit. We 
hope that just like my trip to Baku, the visit of his excellency 
the president of Azerbaijan to Tehran will also be a great 
stride in the expansion of cooperation. [end recording] [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

