<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Islamic Rights Commission To Be Formed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Islamic Rights Commission To Be Formed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2806154294 Tehran IRNA in English 1107 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2806154294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, June 28, IRNA -- A new commission called the 
`Islamic Human Rights Commission' is to be established by the 
judiciary system to follow up issues related to the Islamic 
countries, said Head of the Judiciary Ayatollah Mohammad Yazdi 
here Tuesday [28 June]. 
  Speaking at the closing session of the nationwide seminar on 
`Judiciary Week,' the Ayatollah noted that if faced with any 
case of violation of Islamic human rights inside or outside the 
country, the commission "will have the authority to use its 
capabiities to settle the problem." 
  Addressing the participants, Yazdi described as "acceptable" 
the body's performance in the past five years, adding that the 
judiciary system was looking after people's affairs very 
actively in the said period. 
  Further in his talks, the Ayatollah said that fewer cases 
were referred to the state Supreme Court in the past five years 
and added that some 33,279 inmates have been pardoned in the 
said period. 
  He said his term in office is going to be over, adding that 
he would be happy if the burden were to be shouldered by someone 
else. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

