<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Attorney General Rejects Alleged Rights Abuses </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Attorney General Rejects Alleged Rights Abuses </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2806144594 Tehran IRNA in English 1417 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2806144594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, June 28, IRNA -- No one has gone on trial 
for expressing his thoughts and ideas in the Islamic Republic of 
Iran, Iran's Attorney General Ayatollah Seyyed Abolfazl 
Musavi-Tabrizi reiterated here Tuesday [28 June]. 
  Calling as fabricated the claims on human rights violation 
by 
certain international circles Musavi-Tabrizi declared that the 
most progressive types of human rights were present in the 
Islamic Republic of Iran. 
  Addressing the concluding session of the nationwide seminar 
on judiciary week, Musavi-Tabrizi said that the Islamic system 
will not put aside due punishment as decreed by Islam for 
criminals. 

</TEXT>

