<TEXT>
BFN 

    The following correction pertains to the item headlined 
"Velayati Urges Action Against MKO," published in the 24 June 
Near East &amp; South Asia DAILY REPORT, page 52: 
  Column two, first paragraph, first sentence make read: 
...against the terrorist Munafiqeen Khalq [pejorative reference 
to Mojahedin-e Khalq] outfit (MKO) which was behind the crime. 
  [New paragraph] Foreign Minister 'Ali Akbar Velayati, whose 
official noted [as received] was handed to the OIC secretariat 
in Jeddah, said the terrorist MKO was... (making clear reference 
to "munafiqeen," rewording sentences to clear computer generated 
garble). 

</TEXT>

