<H3> <TI>   Yemeni Minister Arrives With Message From Salih </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yemeni Minister Arrives With Message From Salih </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2606144794 Rabat Moroccan Kingdom Radio Network in Arabic 
1300 GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2606144794 </F>
<F P=104>  Rabat Moroccan Kingdom Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yahya Husayn al-'Arashi, Yemeni minister of civil 
service and administrative reform, arrived in Morocco this 
morning carrying a message from the Yemeni President 'Ali 
'Abdallah Salih, to His Majesty King Hassan II, may God make him 
victorious. 
  The Yemeni official spoke to the radio about this visit, and 
said: 
  [Begin al-'Arashi recording] I have come carrying a message 
from His Excellency Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, 
chairman of the Presidential Council in the Republic of Yemen, 
to his brother His Majesty King Hassan II. 
  As you know, Yemen is going through special circumstances, 
therefore it was necessary to brief his majesty on the 
development of the situation, particularly that the brother 
president attaches special interest to his majesty's 
point-of-view. 
  We also certainly start from the premise that the Kingdom of 
Morocco, king, government, and people, stand beside Yemen and 
its national unity and the unity of its Yemeni territory, 
therefore it is necessary to put them in the picture for more 
consultations over the consultations that are currently taking 
place at the level of the Arab and Yemeni arenas. 
  It is a good opportunity to know the view point and also 
clarify the stance directly. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

