<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Sharif Denies Report on Aden Arms Shipment </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Sharif Denies Report on Aden Arms Shipment </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2806144894 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1400 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2806144894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 28 Jun (MENA)--Information Minister Safwat 
al-Sharif denied press reports that an Egyptian ship carrying 
Saudi weapons to Aden was stopped in the Red Sea before reaching 
its destination. 
  In a statement made today, al-Sharif said: No Egyptian ship 
has been stopped either in the Red Sea or in the Mediterranean 
Sea. He stressed that this report is entirely baseless and 
contradicts Egypt's firm and principled stand on the Yemeni 
problem. He said that Egypt believes the need to immediately 
stop the fighting and to move to the dialogue table. He added 
that Egypt also believes that it is not right to side with one 
party against the other in this problem. 

</TEXT>

