<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official: No Arms Shipped to Rwandan Government </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official: No Arms Shipped to Rwandan Government </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2806121494 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1125 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2806121494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Cairo, 28 Jun (MENA)--Ambassador Sa'id Rif'at, 
assistant foreign minister for African affairs, has again denied 
that Egypt supplied the Rwandan Government with arms. 
  Responding to claims by the Rwandan Patriotic Front that 
Egypt is providing the government with weapons and that Egypt 
has endorsed a Security Council resolution to send troops to 
Rwanda to appease France, Rif'at made a statement today 
affirming that Egypt favors no side to the conflict in Rwanda. 
  He said there is a question mark over the Rwandan Patriotic 
Front's insistence on accusing Egypt of providing the government 
there with weapons despite Egypt's assertion that it is not. 
  He added that Egypt supported Security Council Resolution 
929 
on the intervention of a UN force with a humanitarian task to 
protect the refugees and the displaced in Rwanda relying on 
practical and objective considerations, primarily Egypt's desire 
to ensure protection and security for endangered civilians with 
emphasis on the humanitarian nature of the mission. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

