<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Damascus Declaration Ministers To Meet 5 Jul </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Damascus Declaration Ministers To Meet 5 Jul </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2806152794 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 1400 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2806152794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa has stated that during 
the contacts held among the foreign ministers of the Damascus 
Declaration countries an agreement was reached to convene a new 
round of meetings for the Declaration countries' foreign 
ministers on 5 July 1994 in Kuwait. The foreign ministers will 
discuss issues of interest to the Arab nation, led by 
developments in Yemen and how to end the fighting there. The 
ministers will also discuss how to bolster cooperation in the 
fields stipulated by the Declaration. 
  Foreign Minister Musa also commented on the European Union's 
[EU] Corfu summit statement. In particular, he noted the 
welcome and support expressed in the statement for the contacts 
currently being held with Egypt to find a new agreement between 
Egypt and the EU. He said the EU's agreement was based on talks 
Egypt held with the EU foreign ministers during the meetings of 
the Egyptian-European Cooperation Council in Brussels last 
month. This decision is seen as support for cooperation between 
Egypt and the EU. 

</TEXT>

