<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Security Thwarts `Terrorist' Infiltration </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Security Thwarts `Terrorist' Infiltration </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2806193994 Cairo AL-AHRAM in Arabic 23 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> NC2806193994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo AL-AHRAM </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Security organs have thwarted a terrorist scheme 
planned abroad to carry out sabotage activities against some 
installations and assassinate a number of personalities in 
Egypt. The execution of this plan was entrusted to some 
terrorists who were trained in foreign countries. The State 
Security Investigations' Bureau succeeded in arresting some 
members who were attempting to infiltrate through an Egyptian 
port. It seized all their documents and files, as well as the 
passports the defendants used in their travels to numerous 
countries. 
  A ranking security source told AL-AHRAM correspondent Ahmad 
Musa that confessions by the terrorist group revealed that their 
leadership, which has fled abroad, dispatched them inside the 
country after the successful security blows dealt to terrorist 
leaders 'Awad Siyam and Tal'at Yasin Hammam. The members of 
this group were asked to convey very detailed instructions to 
the terrorist leaders' aides inside, as well as to transfer 
funds. These funds were to be used to carry out terrorist 
operations to make the terrorist presence in the arena known. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

