<H3> <TI>   Lawyers Decide To End Hunger Strike </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Lawyers Decide To End Hunger Strike </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2806175094 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1643 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2806175094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 28 Jun (MENA)--Cairo Lawyers Association 
Chairman 'Abd-al-'Aziz Muhammmad praised yesterday's decision by 
the Public Prosecution Office to release all the lawyers held in 
detention since 17 May following the demonstration at the 
Lawyers Association's premises. 
  Speaking at a news conference today, 'Abd-al-'Aziz said that 
he and the rest of his colleagues who were on a hunger strike 
decided to end their hunger strike immediately after the release 
of the detained lawyers was announced. 
  'Abd-al-'Aziz said that the competent authorities showed 
particular sympathy to the demands of the hunger strikers, chief 
of which was the release of all the lawyers arrested following 
the demonstration. 

</TEXT>

