<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kuwait Supplying Helicopters to Southern Forces </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2906082394 Baghdad INA in Arabic 0650 GMT 29 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2906082394 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa, 29 Jun (INA) -- Competent Yemeni authorities 
have seized three MS-17 military cargo helicopters supplied by 
the rulers of Kuwait to the separatists in southern Yemen. 
Yemeni political sources told INA's correspondent in Sanaa that 
the three helicopters were brought under control recently upon 
landing at one of the airports in Shabwah Governorate, north of 
Aden. 
  The sources said the three helicopters were commanded by 
Yemeni pilots who had recently fled the control of the 
secessionists, along with their families, to seek refuge with 
the forces of legitimacy. 
  Diplomatic sources in Sanaa said the Kuwaiti helicopter deal 
is one of the arms supply deals between the Saudi and Kuwaiti 
regimes and the secessionists in Yemen. 

