<H3> <TI>   Fire Set to South's Only Refinery </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fire Set to South's Only Refinery </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2906104394 Paris AFP in English 1009 GMT 29 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2906104394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Aden, Yemen, June 29 (AFP) -- Attacking northern 
Yemeni warplanes set fire to the south's only oil refinery on 
Wednesday [29 June] as an air and artillery bombardment killed 
eight civilians and wounded 41 here, officials said. 
  A black cloud drifted over Aden from the burning refinery 18 
kilometers (11 miles) to the west. Journalists could not reach 
it because the road has been cut by fighting, but could see the 
fire from here. 
  A southern military spokesman said the refinery was attacked 
by two northern warplanes, while hospital officials said eight 
civilians were killed and 41 wounded in air raids and shelling 
of northern suburbs and other districts. 
  Buildings trembled from the pounding of artillery fire. 
  Oil storage tanks at the refinery were set ablaze three 
weeks 
ago after a northern raid, officials here said. 
  Northern troops loyal to President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih have 
been trying to capture the refinery since they entered the 
western suburbs for the first time on Saturday, cutting off the 
road to the refinery. 
  Northern troops were also in control of Bir Nasr', 15 
kilometres (nine miles) from Aden, where the city's only water 
pumping station is sited. 
  Aden residents have suffered severe water and gasoline 
shortages since the north's advance into the city's suburbs. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

