<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   House Delegation Returns From U.S., France </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    House Delegation Returns From U.S., France </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2806174994 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1600 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2806174994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Al-Khadim al-Wajih, staff member of the House of 
Representatives Speakership, returned to Sanaa today after 
leading a House delegation to the United States and the Republic 
of France. During the visit, the delegation met with several 
U.S. official in Washington to explain what is taking place in 
Yemen and that the current confrontation is between the Yemeni 
people who support unity, legitimacy, and democracy on one hand 
and the rebels who are encroaching on law, the constitution, and 
legitimacy on the other. [words indistinct] 
  In a statement to the Yemeni News Agency, SABA', brother 
al-Khadim al-Wajih said that the Yemeni parliamentary delegation 
sensed an understanding by the U.S. and French sides of the 
House of Representative's position, as well as issues included 
in the messages that House of Representatives Speaker 'Abdallah 
Husayn al- Ahmar addressed to the U.S. Congress and the French 
National Assembly regarding current events in Yemen. 
  The parliamentary delegation also met with the Yemeni 
community in the cities of New York, Detroit, and Buffalo and 
explained to them what is taking place in our country, as well 
as the whole Yemeni people's adherence to unity, constitutional 
legitimacy, and democracy. The delegation sensed during these 
meetings the Yemeni community's support for our country's unity. 
  The parliamentary delegation also met with a number of 
ambassadors of fraternal and friendly countries to the United 
States, explained to them developments in the Republic of Yemen, 
and asked them to urge their countries to support Yemeni unity, 
which is a factor of security and stability for the whole region. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

