<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mubarak Envoy Arrives in Sanaa With Message </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mubarak Envoy Arrives in Sanaa With Message </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2906070794 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0630 GMT 29 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2906070794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa, 29 Jun (MENA) -- Ambassador Badr Hammam, the 
envoy of President Husni Mubarak, arrived in Sanaa this morning 
on a visit to Yemen of several days. 
  Arriving in Sanaa, Ambassador Hammam told MENA's 
correspondent that his visit to Yemen continues the joint 
efforts to contain the situation in Yemen and achieve peace, 
security, and stability for the Yemeni people. 
  He said he was sent by President Mubarak with a message to 
Yemeni President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih and to begin a new round 
of talks with President Salih and the political leaders. We 
hope, God willing, that we achieve our desire of peace and 
stability in Yemen, he said. 

</TEXT>

