<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sha'th Meets With New Israeli Counterpart in Eretz </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sha'th Meets With New Israeli Counterpart in Eretz </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Further on Sha'th Remarks </H4>

<F P=102> JN2806114194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Arabic 1020 GMT 28 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2806114194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Hasan Abu-Zayid from Gaza Eretz checkpoint; from </F>
the "With the Midday Events" program] 
  [Text] The meeting Dr. Nabil Sha'th held with Major General 
Dani Rothschild, coordinator of the Defense Ministry activities 
in the territories, ended a short while ago. This meeting paves 
the way for the resumption of talks between the Israeli and 
Palestinian delegations on the implementation of self-rule in 
the rest of the West Bank. The most important topics discussed 
by the two were the release of Palestinian prisoners, the border 
crossing points, and the presence of Palestinian police at them. 
Dr. Nabil Sha'th spoke to us a short while ago: 
  [Begin Sha'th recording] I believe such meetings are very 
useful to declare and actually draw up plans for the next phase 
of negotiations on Palestinian authority in the West Bank. This 
required a comprehensive assessment of what was implemented thus 
far. This basically included the problem of prisoners and those 
released -- a problem which is of concern to every Palestinian 
citizen. We also discussed the problem of the implementation of 
security, secure passage, border posts, international presence, 
and a quadruple committee meeting to discuss the problem of 
refugees. All these issues were discussed, in addition to an 
assessment of the economic situation, Palestinian labor force in 
Israel, and the easing of restrictions on Gaza and other 
Palestinian areas. We made a comprehensive assessment. Some 
solutions and the role of the security coordination committee 
and the civil coordination committee in solving these problems 
were discussed. 
  Regarding the negotiations, I cannot talk about any details 
because we have actually agreed to several points. We have to 
refer to President 'Arafat before any of them can be publicized. 
We have also agreed to prepare for President 'Arafat's meeting 
with Prime Minister Rabin and Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres in 
Paris on 7 July. Consequently, the beginning of negotiations 
and formation of committees and the Palestinian-Israeli summit 
were the subject of our planning. I will be satisfied with this 
because I cannot answer questions on the venue, time, and 
details because these all first require the approval of 
President 'Arafat. Naturally, General Rothschild will also 
consult with his leadership for the same reason. I think the 
meeting was positive and I hope it will herald the start of a 
new stage in the peace process. [end recording] 
  Maj. Gen. Dani Rothschild said after the meeting that the 
Israeli and Palestinian sides will prepare for a meeting between 
Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin and Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres 
on the one hand, and PLO Chairman Yasir 'Arafat on 7 July on the 
other. The start of negotiations between Israel and the 
Palestinians on the implementation of self-rule in the rest of 
the West Bank will then be announced. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-38259 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes125dd_94004" </HT>


