<H3> <TI>   Sha'th Notes Discussion Topics With Israel's Sarid </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sha'th Notes Discussion Topics With Israel's Sarid </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2806204494 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 2000 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2806204494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Dr. Nabil Sha'th, minister of planning and 
international cooperation in the Palestinian National Authority, 
will arrive in Cairo later tonight. 
  Dr. Sha'th launched a new round of Palestinian-Israeli talks 
with a meeting with Israeli Environment Minister Yosi Sarid 
today. The Palestinian minister said that today's talks dealt 
with the steps taken to implement the self-rule agreement. 
These, he added, include the release of Palestinian detainees, 
the transfer of civilian authority to Palestinians, the 
withdrawal of Israeli forces, the holding of legislative 
elections before the end of September, and the date and venue of 
subsequent talks. 

</TEXT>

