<F P=101> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Expected To Move to Jericho Mid-Jul </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat Expected To Move to Jericho Mid-Jul </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2806154494 London AL-HAYAH in Arabic 28 Jun 94 p5 </F>
<F P=103> PM2806154494 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-HAYAH </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Rashid Khashanah: "Fatah Central Committee Urges </F>
'Arafat To Move to Jericho"] 
  [Text] Tunis -- An informed Palestinian source has told 
AL-HAYAH that members of Fatah's Central Committee tried hard to 
persuade President Yasir 'Arafat to move to the autonomy areas. 
These attempts were made during the Central Committee meeting in 
Tunis last Saturday [18 June]. The meeting was devoted to 
discussion of completion of the arrangements for transporting 
some of Fatah's cadres to the Gaza Strip and the Jericho area. 
  The source said that 'Arafat did not give a specific answer 
to the members' request but they understood that he linked his 
decision to the results of the visit of Ahmad Quray' 
(Abu-'Ala'), head of the PLO's Economic Department and economy 
minister in the Palestinian Authority, to the United States and 
his talks with World Bank officials on the aid the bank intends 
to give the Palestinian Authority. 
  A Fatah Central Committee member said that 'Arafat would 
probably move to Jericho around the middle of next month after 
his visit to Paris on 6 July to receive the Houphouet-Boigny 
peace prize along with Israeli Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin and 
Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres, and after a clear and accurate 
picture emerges about the financial situation of the Palestinian 
Authority in the light of the meeting of the donor states in the 
second week of July. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

