<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Orders Committee Report on Gaza, Jericho </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat Orders Committee Report on Gaza, Jericho </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2806124794 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1225 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2806124794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tunis, 28 Jun (MENA) -- Palestinian President Yasir 
'Arafat has issued a decree forming a committee chaired by Yahya 
Khalaf, head of the PLO's Cultural Department, to travel to the 
Palestinian autonomy region to learn about the situation there 
at first hand and prepare a report to be presented to the 
Palestinian leadership. 
  Yahya Khalaf stated that the Palestinian leadership will 
study this report in light of which it will make its final 
decision on who should return to Gaza and Jericho immediately 
and who should wait until special arrangements to return are 
made. 
  He said the committee, which includes Jamil Shihadah, 
secretary general of the Palestinian Teachers Union, and Rawhi 
Futuhi, secretary of the Palestinian popular organizations, will 
travel to Amman later today en route to Jericho and then the 
Gaza Strip to prepare the report and present it to the 
Palestinian leadership within three days. 

</TEXT>

