<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Appoints Committee To Manage Nablus Affairs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat Appoints Committee To Manage Nablus Affairs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2806180194 Algiers Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1702 GMT 
28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2806180194 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Voice of Palestine </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President 'Arafat, chairman of the PLO executive 
committee and chairman of the Palestinian National Authority, 
today decided that a provisional committee be set up to manage 
the municipality of Nablus, whose task will be to manage the 
administration of the municipality in accordance with the 
provisions of municipality laws and regulations, and to make 
preparations for municipal elections in the town. The work of 
the committee will last one year during which the elections will 
be held. Here are the names of the brother members of the 
provisional committees: lawyer Ghassan Walid al-Shak'a, Dr. 
Hatim Jamil Kamal, engineer Hani Tawfiq 'Arafat, engineer Adnan, 
Umar al-Dirhalli, Azzam Muhammad Sa'id al-Alul, Samir Sadiq 
Qadri, engineer Abbas Muhammad Hasan Jabir, agricultural 
engineer 'Amid Wahid al-Masri, Ibrahim Sa'id Shikha, Khaldun 
Bakr 'Abd al-Haq, Dr. Amin Haddad, Muhammad Yusif Shahin, 
engineer Mufid Adil Nabulsi, Asim Ghalib Salim, Salih Rushdi 
'Abd al-Hadi, and brother Saliq Nasuh Kan'an. 

</TEXT>

