<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   FIDA on Delay in 'Arafat Arrival in Autonomy Area </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    FIDA on Delay in 'Arafat Arrival in Autonomy Area </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2806135194 Jerusalem AL-QUDS in Arabic 26 Jun 94 p 23 </F>
<F P=103> TA2806135194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem AL-QUDS </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Jerusalem, QUDS PRESS -- A Palestinian party 
participating in the Palestinian self-rule authority council has 
criticized PLO Executive Committee Chairman Yasir 'Arafat's 
delay in coming to the self-rule areas in the Gaza Strip and 
Jericho. 
  A statement by the Palestinian Democratic Union, FIDA, said 
that this delay, whatever its justification or reason, causes 
harmful effects on the unity of the Palestinian leadership's 
performance in various spheres and on the clarity of the plan of 
action. It also paralyzes the capacity of members of the 
national authority in carrying out their responsibilities as a 
collective team. 
  The party hinted at withdrawing from the authority and 
pointed out that "its support for and continued participation in 
the authority depends on the its possession of a comprehensive 
national plan to pursue the battle of independence; on the 
realization of adequate participation, justice, and equality; 
and on the granting of freedom." The statement also called for 
accelerating the completion of the authority's domain. 
  The party is currently represented in the authority council 
by its secretary general, Yasir 'Abd-Rabbuh, who holds the 
education and arts portfolio, and Dr. 'Azmi al-Shu'aybi, who 
holds the youth and sport portfolio. 

</TEXT>

