<H3> <TI>   Issue of al-Yarmuk Waters To Be Broached With Syria </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Issue of al-Yarmuk Waters To Be Broached With Syria </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2806185594 Amman AKHIR KHABAR in Arabic 28-29 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN2806185594 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AKHIR KHABAR </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A responsible source has revealed that the 
government will broach the issue of the joint waters of the 
al-Yarmuk River with Syria after reaching an agreement with 
Israel in the talks slated to be held in the region next month. 
  The source, which requested anonymity, added that Jordan 
feels that it is being done an injustice by the Syrian 
practices, particularly since Syria is monopolizing the use of 
the al-Yarmuk River tributaries by building dams on them. The 
source noted that Jordan was sympathetic with the Syrian 
position before the start of the peace process. But, now, Syria 
must seriously examine our grievances, the source said. 

</TEXT>

