First Program Network in Persian 0230 GMT 29 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2906054194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] For the first time since the Yemeni battles started, 
representatives of the conflicting sides met in New York 
yesterday. AFP reports that the two sides could not set a date 
for a cease-fire. The talks, which were held in the presence of 
Lakhdar Brahimi, the UN secretary general's special envoy for 
Yemeni affairs, were attended by 'Abd al-Karim al-Iryani, 
Yemen's planning and development minister, representing the 
northern forces, and Haydar Abu Bakr al-'Attas, representing the 
southern forces. 
  The official Yemeni news agency has reported that 'Ali Salim 
al-Bid, who was living in al-Mukalla in east Aden, was wounded 
and has gone to an Arab country for treatment. The news agency 
has not revealed the name of the Arab country. 
  Another report citing the official Yemeni news agency states 
that Yemeni President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih has accused the 
southerners of trying to internationalize the Yemeni war. 
Speaking with Egyptian President Husni Mubarak on the phone 
yesterday, he said the southerners are thus trying to achieve 
their expansionist objectives. 

</TEXT>

