<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Israel Allows Fatah Leaders in Self-Rule Area </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Israel Allows Fatah Leaders in Self-Rule Area </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN3006095594 Amman AL-DUSTUR in Arabic 30 Jun 94 pp 1, 28 </F>
<F P=103> JN3006095594 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-DUSTUR </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Tawfiq 'Abid] </F>
  [Excerpt] Israeli authorities have approved the return of 
all Fatah Central Committee members to the self-rule area. 
AL-DUSTUR has learned that 15 Central Committee members will 
accompany President Yasir 'Arafat when he returns to the Gaza 
Strip. 
  Informed sources have told AL-DUSTUR that the Israeli 
authorities have excluded Major General Muhammad Jihad from 
those who were allowed to return. Maj. Gen. Muhammad Jihad 
leads the hardliners within Fatah who oppose negotiations with 
Israel and any agreements that result from them. 
  The informed military sources said this hardline trend 
comprises many military people. It works within Fatah against 
the negotiations and is active at Fatah Central Committee and 
Revolutionary Council meetings in support of a reinvigorated 
intifadah. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

