<H3> <TI>   Slovakia To Provide 250 `Advanced' Tanks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Slovakia To Provide 250 `Advanced' Tanks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN3006080794 Amman AL-DUSTUR in Arabic 30 Jun 94 p 29 </F>
<F P=103> JN3006080794 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-DUSTUR </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Exclusive" report by 'Ali Jamalu] </F>
  [Excerpt] A Western diplomatic source has said that Slovak 
Foreign Minister Eduard Kukan, who visited Damascus last week 
and met with senior Syrian officials, has signed an agreement 
with the Syrian side stipulating the sale of 250 tanks of an 
advanced type to Syria. 
  The source said Damascus is continuing to modernize the 
weaponary of its military institutions by both old and new 
relations with several non-Western nations, including Russia, 
the PRC, Korea, India, and now Slovakia, which inherited huge 
weapons factories from the mother country (Czechoslovakia). 
  The source said this policy is based on Damascus' view that 
"comprehensive peace," stipulated by the resolutions of 
international legitimacy and the land-for-peace principle, is 
facing deliberate Israeli obstruction. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

