<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> United Arab Emirates </F>
<H3> <TI>   Forces Seize Iranian Boat, Infiltrators </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Forces Seize Iranian Boat, Infiltrators </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2906151594 London AL-HAYAH in Arabic 29 Jun 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> PM2906151594 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-HAYAH </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Shafiq al-Asadi: "Emirates Seize Boat Carrying </F>
Iranian Infiltrators"] 
  [Excerpts] Abu Dhabi -- Border and coast guard forces in 
the United Arab Emirates [UAE] have seized a boat carrying 
Iranian infiltrators who were trying to anchor off the UAE coast 
in the emirate of Umm al-Qaywayn, at a time when the UAE is 
taking decisive measures to foil infiltration operations and 
tackle the imbalance in the population structure. 
  A spokesman for the border guard forces confirmed that the 
boat was seized after border guard forces opened fire on it and 
after a chase in the Gulf in which Interior Ministry helicopters 
took part. 
  The spokesman said that none of the infiltrators was hurt, 
the boat has been handed over to border guard forces, and the 
infiltrators have been referred to the judiciary for legal 
proceedings to be taken against them. 
  The UAE is currently taking tough measures to foil 
infiltration incidents conducted by various types of boats which 
anchor off its coasts along the Gulf and the Gulf of Oman. 
[passage omitted] 
  The UAE Interior Ministry said in a statement distributed 
yesterday that border and coast guard forces, supported by 
police helicopters, foiled an attempt to infiltrate into the UAE 
by a speedboat which was trying to anchor off the coast of Umm 
al-Qaywayn. 
  The statement said the boat was fired on but no one was 
hurt, 
and the boat was seized and all the people on board were 
arrested. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

