<H3> <TI>   Salih: Forces `In Control' of 55 Percent of Aden </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Salih: Forces `In Control' of 55 Percent of Aden </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN3006053794 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0430 GMT 30 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN3006053794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, 
Presidential Council chairman and supreme commander of the Armed 
Forces, has emphasized that the Republic of Yemen will deal 
positively with any international proposal that is in interest 
of the Yemeni people and that serves the higher national 
interest. 
  He said: Our forces -- the forces of legitimacy -- have 
restored more than 70 percent of the areas that had been 
controlled by the secessionists. He said that the forces of 
legitimacy are now at the entrances of Hadramaut, and are in 
control of more than 55 percent of city of Aden. 
  The brother president emphasized our Yemeni people's 
rejection of those secessionists and agents who betrayed their 
people and sold the homeland's cause at a low price. 
  He called on some brotherly countries, which claim to be 
really eager to save Yemeni blood, to stop interfering in our 
internal affairs and not to support the rebels. 
  The brother president hailed the position of the fraternal 
State of Qatar -- government and people -- which advocates 
Yemeni unity, and the Qatari leadership's sympathy with, and 
support for legitimacy and Yemeni people. 
  He said this in a (television interview?) with the Qatari 
television team. 

</TEXT>

