<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Salih Receives Egyptian Envoy, Message </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Salih Receives Egyptian Envoy, Message </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2906182594 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1700 GMT 29 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2906182594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, 
chairman of the Presidential Council, received today brother 
Badr Hammam, assistant to the foreign minister of fraternal 
Egypt, who conveyed a message to the brother president from his 
brother Egyptian President Muhammad Husni Mubarak. The message 
deals with developments in our country, as well as issues of 
interest to the brotherly relations between the two countries. 
  The message stresses Egypt's firm position and support for 
Yemeni unity, cease-fire efforts, and dialogue within the 
framework of unity as the best way to settle the current 
differences. It also asserts that Egypt is with unity, with the 
people, and with stability in the Republic of Yemen. 
  The Presidential Council chairman voiced his satisfaction 
with and great appreciation for the position of the brothers in 
Egypt, headed by His Excellency President Muhammad Husni 
Mubarak. He referred to the special Yemeni-Egyptian relations 
and the profound and strong ties between the two fraternal 
countries. He also said that Egypt's support for the Yemeni 
people and their unity is part of its honorable pan-Arab role 
[words indistinct] in support of the eternal Yemeni revolution. 

</TEXT>

