<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Interior Minister Salamah Hammad has emphasized 
that the security situation in Jordan is very good, and said 
there is not even one political prisoner. 
  In a news conference at the Interior Ministry today, the 
interior minister added that the allegations that prisons are 
full of detainees are baseless. Only those who committed 
criminal actions are in prison, and no prisoner is detained 
without a decision by the general prosecutor. 
  He said public liberties in Jordan are preserved in a 
democratic atmosphere that is unique in the region. 
  Hammad said that detention measures, including those who 
committed the crimes of explosions in public places, have been 
carried out in accordance with the law and within the framework 
of legal procedures. [passage omitted] 

