<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Dudayev Says Attempt on Life `Sabotage' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Dudayev Says Attempt on Life `Sabotage' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2805193194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1815 
GMT 28 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2805193194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Sharip Ausuyev] </F>
  [Excerpts] Groznyy, 28 May -- Chechen President Dzhokhar 
Dudayev described yesterday's terrorist act in the republic as 
carefully organized sabotage directed against independent 
Chechnya. He said on local television today that forces opposed 
to the slight thaw in Russo-Chechen relations were behind this 
act. 
  Some details about the terrorist act emerged today. There 
was a powerful explosion at about 2000 local time on 27 May on 
the road between the Chechen settlements of Zakan-Lirk and 
Alkha-Kala just as the president's motorcade was driving past a 
Zhiguli model nine parked at the edge of the road. [passage 
omitted] 
  Yaragi Mamodayev, head of the government of national 
confidence, also gave his opinion about the terrorist act today. 
In a statement he stressed that the process of the 
self-destruction of the Chechen people is becoming more 
profound. The government of national confidence resolutely 
condemns such actions, no matter by whom, and appeals to the 
leaders of the regime, to all sociopolitical forces and to the 
citizens of the republic for nationwide reconciliation and an 
end to all forms of confrontation. 

</TEXT>

