<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Intelligence Denies Role in Attack </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Intelligence Denies Role in Attack </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3005145694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1413 GMT 30 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3005145694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Viktor Khrekov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 30 TASS -- Russian foreign intelligence 
has denied involvement in attack on Chechen President Dzhokhar 
Dudayev this past weekend. 
  Foreign intelligence spokeswoman Tatyana Samolis described 
as 
groundless a statement by head of the Chechen department of the 
press and information Movladi Udugov made in an interview with 
FRANCE PRESSE that "local experts made an attempt on Dzhokhar 
Dudayev's life on the order from (Russian foreign intelligence 
chief) Yevgeniy Primakov." 
  In an interview with ITAR-TASS on Monday, Samolis said that 
such allegations are a "fabrication bordering on nonsense and 
absurdity." She said the Russian foreign intelligence abandoned 
terroristic methods long ago and does not even have structures 
which could carry out such activity. 
  The foreign intelligence service only collects information, 
she said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

