<H3> <TI>   Russian Troops Said on Move </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Troops Said on Move </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3005190794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1736 GMT 30 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3005190794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A senior official in the Chechen State Security 
Department said that Russian troops were on the move in areas 
bordering on Chechnya. 
  The department's deputy head Khamid Dzhalmaldayev said that, 
according to the Chechen general staff, a Su-27 attack plane 
unit had flown to the air base in Mozdok, North Ossetia. 
  He added that Russian Interior Ministry special troops whose 
fire power is equal to that of a wartime infantry division had 
moved into the Prigorodnyy District of North Ossetia. 
  Dzhalmaldayev thought that these troop movement had to do 
with the latest events such as the attempt on Dzhokhar Dudayev's 
life and efforts mounted by the Russian special services to 
destabilize Chechnya. 
  Meanwhile, defense, interior and security chiefs told a 
conference chaired by Chechen President Dudayev that the 
situation in the republic was under control. 

</TEXT>

