<H3> <TI>   N. Ossetian President Leaves for Moscow Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    N. Ossetian President Leaves for Moscow Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2905141394 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1302 
GMT 29 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2905141394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Shanayev] </F>
  [Text] Vladikavkaz, 29 May -- The extension of the state of 
emergency in some areas of North Ossetia for another two months 
currently serves as a guarantee of the safety of the republic's 
citizens, North Ossetia's President Akhsarbek Galazov told 
ITAR-TASS today. He strongly rejected the idea of introducing 
federal government in Prigorodnyy Rayon. This will be, in his 
opinion, a deadlock that may cause a new tragedy in the North 
Caucasus. Galazov left for Moscow today to take part in a 
meeting of the Federation Council, which will consider the 
situation in the zone of the Ossetian-Ingush conflict and the 
extension of the state of emergency in some parts of North 
Ossetia and Ingushetia. 
  The president believes that peaceful negotiations should be 
the main thrust in settling relations between the peoples of 
North Ossetia and Ingushetia. 

</TEXT>

