<H3> <TI>   State of Emergency Imposed in N. Ossetia, Ingushetia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    State of Emergency Imposed in N. Ossetia, Ingushetia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3005162094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1526 GMT 30 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3005162094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow May 30 TASS -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin signed a decree on Monday imposing a state of emergency 
in parts of North Ossetia and Ingushetia. 
  The state of emergency will be imposed from 14:00 on May 31, 
1994 till 14:00 July 31, 1994. 
  The decree also lifts as of 14:00 May 31 the state of 
emergency imposed by the presidential decrees of April 4 and 
April 27, 1994. 
  The decree comes into effect from the day it is signed, the 
presidential press service said. 

</TEXT>

