  [Text] Boris Yeltsin signed a decree today extending the 
state of emergency in the Ingush-Ossetian conflict zone to the 
Malgobekskiy and Sunzhenskiy Rayons of Ingushetia. This decree 
has to be approved by the Federation Council. It is worth 
mentioning that Boris Yeltsin's actions will provoke a strongly 
negative reaction in Groznyy. Here these rayons are considered 
to be historically Chechen lands. This is what (Mavlen 
Salimov), an aide to the president of Chechnya, said to Radio 
Ekho Moskvy about this: 
  [Begin Salimov recording] We consider that these actions are 
unlawful, and consider them as aggression, as an attempted act 
of aggression. [end recording] 
