<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Briefs Tatar Officials on Fighting Crime </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Briefs Tatar Officials on Fighting Crime </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3005191994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1905 GMT 30 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3005191994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Tamara Zamyatina, Yuriy Sizov, </F>
and Nikolay Sorokin] 
  [Text] Naberezhnye Chelny May 30 TASS--Fighting organised 
crime in Russia must become a top priority task, Russian 
President Boris Yeltsin said. 
  Speaking at a meeting with the leaders of Tatarstan's law 
enforcement bodies on Monday, Yeltsin called for working out a 
legislative framework for the implementation of the federal 
programme of combating organised crime in Russia adopted last 
week. 
  He said special attention should be paid to fighting 
corruption, machinations in the credit and monetary system, tax 
evasion and illegal deals with privatisation vouchers. 

</TEXT>

