<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Commission Inspects Pacific Border Troops Readiness </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Commission Inspects Pacific Border Troops Readiness </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW3105081694 Vladivostok Radiostantsiya Tikhiy Okean 
Maritime Network in Russian 0715 GMT 27 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW3105081694 </F>
<F P=104>  Vladivostok Radiostantsiya Tikhiy Okean 
Maritime Network </F>

<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Pacific Ocean" Program] </F>
  [Text] Lieutenant General Aleksey Shcherbakov, deputy 
commander of the Russian border troops, headed an inspection 
commission which carried out a systematic survey of the defense 
of Russia's Pacific Ocean border. He held a news conference in 
Vladivostok, at which he said that troops of the Pacific Border 
District were in a state of good combatreadiness. The 
inspectors had the opportunity to witness with their own eyes 
that the eastern border protected by the Pacific troops was 
still strong and secure -- the district's border guards detained 
35 transgressors, uncovered and prevented 63 attempts to use 
counterfeit passports at border crossings, and seized a large 
contraband shipment of choice seafood delicacies, which domestic 
businessmen attempted to export to Japan illegally. 
  The chairman of the inspection commission said: "We 
evaluated 
the situation in the border district strictly and impartially. 
Practically every aspect of the condition of the troops was 
examined, and in spite of the numerous problems, all troops and 
units of the district cope well with the goal of protecting the 
border, and the state of morale of the officers and personnel is 
praiseworthy." 

</TEXT>

