<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ukraine's Ministry of Defense press service reports 
the details of Minister Vitaliy Radetskyy's official visit to 
Brussels. He held intensive talks with his counterparts from 
Slovakia, Lithuania, Albania, Moldova, and Poland. These 
meetings focused on issues concerning European security, 
cooperation within the Partnership for Peace program, and ways 
of bilateral cooperation in the military sphere. A number of 
important agreements were reached with regard to joint military 
training and exchange of delegations. 
  The defense ministers of the above countries expressed 
concern at the developments in Crimea. They supported Ukraine's 
stance on the issue and proposals voiced by Radetskyy for a 
settlement on the Crimean peninsula. In this context they 
agreed that Ukraine was justified in raising the issue of fair 
division of the Black Sea Fleet and its deployment. 

</TEXT>

