<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Turkish Delegation Arrives for Talks in Kiev </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Turkish Delegation Arrives for Talks in Kiev </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Demirel Expresses Support </H4>

<F P=102> LD3005191794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1736 GMT 30 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3005191794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Turkey is ready to use its influence over NATO, the 
European Union and the UN to support the territorial integrity 
of Ukraine and the presence of Crimea within Ukraine. This was 
disclosed to the press by the leader of the Crimean Tartar 
Mejlis Mustafa Jamilev who met Turkish President Suleyman 
Demirel in Kiev on Monday. 
  According to Jamilev, Ukraine has made much greater 
concessions to Crimean separatists than it should have. He was 
satisfied with the fact that now Kiev holds a tougher, 
principled approach to Crimea. The head of the Mejlis called 
Crimea an illegal republic of colonists. 
  He said that the future course of development in Crimea 
depends on how much Russia and other neighbors are going to 
respect the territorial integrity of Ukraine. Jamilev said 
there are signs today that Russia will continue interfering in 
the situation. 
  In his opinion, the pressure of the world community could 
have a certain effect keeping Russia from actions that 
destabilize the situation in the Crimea. 
  Jamilev said the Turkish president promised to finance the 
construction of about 1000 apartments for Crimean Tatars. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

