<F P=106> [Quotation marks as received] </F>
  [Text] Sevastopol, 28 May -- "For the first time the 
negotiating process is proceeding constructively, Vice Admiral 
Volodymyr Bezkorovaynyy, Ukraine's Navy Commander, reported at a 
news conference on the results of the latest Russian-Ukrainian 
Black Sea Fleet talks, which he conducted on 27 May. The 
Russian side has taken up a softer position. The fact that for 
the first time we are discussing details in depth and are 
working on each facility in detail adds optimism. The Russian 
delegation was discussing issues that it had avoided at the 
talks in Sevastopol. One feels that Russia's delegation has a 
purpose: To resolve the issue," Mr. Bezkorovaynyy emphasized. 

