<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   G-7 Experts, Government Discuss Nuclear Power Aid </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    G-7 Experts, Government Discuss Nuclear Power Aid </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3105102594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0954 GMT 31 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3105102594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Viktor Demidenko and Mikhail </F>
Melnik] 
  [Text] Kiev May 31 TASS -- Financial assistance to Ukraine 
in the construction of new nuclear power stations, so that the 
Chernobyl station could be shut down, was discussed during a 
closed door meeting between Group-of-Seven experts and a 
Ukrainian Government delegation here on Tuesday. 
  According to well-informed sources, the international group 
of experts, after a series of meetings and consultations and the 
study of the situation, will prepare a report with due regard 
for the Ukrainian Government's wishes. 
  The report will serve as the basis of a project for 
assistance to Kiev. The project is then to be considered at a 
working meeting of G-7 representatives in Rome in June. 
  A specific `nuclear assistance' programme is to be discussed 
at a regular G-7 summit in Naples in July. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

