<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kiev To Submit Foreign Trade Memorandum to GATT </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kiev To Submit Foreign Trade Memorandum to GATT </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2905143294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1231 GMT 29 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2905143294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ukraine intends to officially submit a memorandum 
on foreign trade regulations to GATT at the end of June. This 
was announced to the press on Saturday by the Ukrainian Minister 
for Foreign Economic Relations Oleg Slepichev. 
  On Friday a government conference on Ukraine's membership in 
GATT ended in Kiev. It was attended by a GATT delegation led by 
the head of the commission on Ukraine's admission Andrew Stoller. 
  According to Slepichev, among other things participants 
pointed to the need to harmonize the foreign economic 
legislation of Ukraine with GATT norms. The need was stressed to 
change laws regulating investments and taxes. 
  Slepichev said Ukraine's foreign partners are alarmed by 
constant alterations of Ukrainian legislation. 
  Meanwhile, Stoller said that after the conference the 
American government intends to offer Ukraine technical 
assistance in harmonizing its legislation. 

</TEXT>

