<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk Criticizes Moscow TV Coverage </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kravchuk Criticizes Moscow TV Coverage </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2905150694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1231 GMT 29 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2905150694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Ostankino TV company covers relations between 
Ukraine and Russia tendentiously. It does not provide authentic 
information and therefore fails to promote neighborly ties 
between the two countries. President Leonid Kravchuk made this 
statement on Saturday, commenting at journalists' request on the 
decision to deprive several Ostankino reporters of their 
accreditation in Ukraine. 
  Earlier the press service of Ukraine's Foreign Ministry 
deprived Ostankino reporters in Donetsk, Kharkov and Odessa of 
their accreditation. 
  Nevertheless, President Kravchuk said that Ukraine is not 
against a unified information space. It only wants the coverage 
of events in that space to be objective. 
  Leonid Kravchuk also criticized some Ukrainian news media 
for 
having a penchant for "hot" facts and for failing to present a 
complete picture of developments and processes in Ukraine. He 
did not specify precisely what publications he meant. 

</TEXT>

