<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official Explains Decision on `Ostankino' Correspondents </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official Explains Decision on `Ostankino' Correspondents </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2705160894 Kiev URYADOVYY KURYER in Ukrainian 26 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU2705160894 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev URYADOVYY KURYER </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "`Ostankino' Correspondents Have Been </F>
Denied Accreditation"] 
  [Text] Ukraine's Ministry of Foreign Affairs has adopted a 
decision to deprive correspondents of the "Ostankino" television 
company who work in Ukraine of their accreditation. This was 
stated to UKRINFORM by Yuriy Serhyeyev, chief of the Information 
Administration at Ukraine's Ministry of Foreign Affairs. He 
pointed out that the decision had been adopted in view of the 
actions, which are incompatible with international concepts of 
information. The representative of the Ministry of Foreign 
Affairs also stated that the decision had been adopted following 
"the provocative coverage of events in Odessa, the Crimea, and 
in Eastern Ukraine." All of this led us to adopt such a 
decision, he said. We are not depriving these mass media of a 
possibility to work, but we want information carried by them to 
be objective. 

</TEXT>

