<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Grachev: Russia To Join NATO Program in 2-3 Weeks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Grachev: Russia To Join NATO Program in 2-3 Weeks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3005144794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1405 GMT 30 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3005144794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Mikhail Shevtsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 30 TASS -- Russia intends to join NATO's 
Partnership for Peace Programme in two to three weeks, Russian 
Defence Minister Pavel Grachev said. 
  Speaking at a meeting with parliamentary state secretary of 
the German Defence Ministry Michaela Geiger in Moscow on Monday, 
Grachev said that the final date of signing will depend on how 
soon Russia's proposals are considered and approved by NATO. 
  Grachev stressed that the results of his visit to Brussels 
and his speech at the NATO headquarters have been approved by 
Russian President Boris Yeltsin. He added that technical 
aspects of Russia's accession to the programme will be ironed 
out through diplomatic channels. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

