<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Departs Paris European Stability Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kozyrev Departs Paris European Stability Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2705161894 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1445 
GMT 27 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2705161894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS special correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Paris, 27 May -- Russian Foreign Minister Andrey 
Kozyrev, who has taken part in the two-day international 
conference here to work out a pact on stability in Europe, has 
left Paris's Orly airport for Moscow. 
  In a conversation with an ITAR-TASS correspondent not long 
before his departure, he said that "Russia supported the French 
initiative for the conclusion of this pact, helped to implement 
and formulate the initiative, and assisted the success of the 
Paris conference." Delegations from 57 states and international 
organizations took part in the conference. 

</TEXT>

