<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Comments on Russian-European Partnership Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Comments on Russian-European Partnership Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2705212294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1953 GMT 27 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2705212294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Dmitriy Gorokhov, Andrey </F>
Krasnoshchekov, and Andrey Shtorkh] 
  [Text] Paris May 27 TASS -- "The signing of an agreement on 
Russian-European partnership will be a major Russian step to 
Europe," Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev told ITAR-TASS 
correspondent while in Paris to attend an international 
conference on a stability pact. 
  In the words of Kozyrev, much work has been done to finalize 
the document, and it is clear already now the document will be 
fundamental. Technical details will be coordinated and the 
document will be edited and translated into languages of 
states-members of the European Union. 
  The minister did not exclude experts may fail to do this job 
by the next session of the European Union to be held in June. 
That is why, the agreement will be signed later, and initialed 
in June. He stressed "there is no need to hurry, since the 
basic agreement to sign the document has been reached". 
  The Russian-European agreement is very important from the 
political point of view, stressed the minister. This document 
will provide for the future form of all Russian-European 
relations. The agreement envisages a system of political 
consultations, a mechanism of political interaction. Under the 
document, summit meeting with the leaders of the "European 
Three" will be held at least once in two years, and contacts 
between ministers will be regular. 
  A major aspect of the agreement is that it opens way "to 
gradual but decisive Russian entrance to the world markets of 
goods, including products of the nuclear cycle, services, 
capital and labor", said the minister. The document will lay 
down the basis for fundamental political and economic 
interaction between Russia and the European Union, he said. 

</TEXT>

