<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reportage on Chernomyrdin PRC Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reportage on Chernomyrdin PRC Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Talks With Jiang Zemin </H4>

<F P=102> LD2705185694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1244 
GMT 27 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2705185694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS special correspondent] </F>
  [Excerpts] Beijing, 27 May -- Jiang Zemin, chairman of the 
People's Republic of China, accepted Russian Federation 
President Boris Yeltsin's invitation to make an official visit 
to Russia with great enthusiasm, Russian Prime Minister Viktor 
Chernomyrdin announced at a news conference in Beijing on the 
second day of his visit. [passage omitted] 
  Chernomyrdin said: "We were unanimous in the view that 
relations between our countries are on a firm path towards 
constructive partnership on a broad range of bilateral and 
international problems." 
  The prime minister believes that China can play an important 
role in opening up Siberia and the Far East. The possibility of 
Russia participating in the reconstruction and modernization of 
industrial enterprises built with the help of the USSR in the 
1950's was discussed, along with the building of the "three 
gorge" hydroscheme power installations. The sides agreed to 
lift obstacles hindering joint enterprise, investment 
cooperation, and other forms of direct partnership. [passage 
omitted] 
  The exchange of views during the talks and meetings with the 
Chinese leadership on the main issues in the world showed that 
the views of China and Russia on the main international issues 
coincide, or are close, the Russian prime minister said. 
Constructive inter- relations in regional and world affairs, he 
said, are an important factor for stability and security in Asia 
and general improvement of the situation in the world as a whole. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

