<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kokoshin Comments on PRC Military Cooperation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kokoshin Comments on PRC Military Cooperation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3005140994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1252 GMT 30 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3005140994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russia's First Deputy Defense Minister Andrey 
Kokoshin is convinced that the Chinese market is lucrative for 
Moscow and is ready "to consume Russian systems of armaments." 
He told this to Interfax at the end of the talks he conducted 
in Beijing as a member of a Russian Government delegation that 
accompanied Premier Viktor Chernomyrdin in his official visit to 
China. 
  Kokoshin explained that the systems of arms available in 
China today had been patterned on Soviet weapon designs. 
  He reported that a contract to sell 26 SU-27 war planes to 
China was already being implemented. He described SU-27 as a 
"good machine, which will apparently be in service until 
2020-2025, under conditions of essential modernization." He 
added that there were plans to equip this fighter plane with new 
on-board arms. 
  He said that his negotiating partner in Beijing was General 
Liu Huangquing, a vice-chairman of China's Central Military 
Council. In Kokoshin's assessment, "military cooperation has 
been going well with close contacts between border military 
districts and extensive delegation exchanges." He revealed that 
the Chinese defense minister is to visit Moscow soon. Chinese 
servicemen are expected at Russian military academies, and 
Russian Army officers are to undergo training in China. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

