<H3> <TI>   Vietnamese Military Reportedly Discuss Arms Sales With DPRK </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Vietnamese Military Reportedly Discuss Arms Sales With DPRK </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3005101694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0740 
GMT 30 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3005101694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Aleksandr Valiyev] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, 30 May (ITAR-TASS) -- A military 
delegation from Vietnam paid an unannounced visit to the DPRK 
this month. The talks with the North Korean side covered a 
number of issues, primarily the coming visit of the Vietnamese 
defense minister to Pyongyang on 16 June, informed sources told 
ITAR-TASS. The sources said the visit should have taken place 
three days ago but was postponed for undisclosed reasons. 
  The republic's mass media said nothing about the Vietnamese 
military delegation's visit. Local observers believe that the 
sides are also making arrangements for the sale of rifles and 
other arms manufactured in the north of the Korean peninsula. 
  Representatives of the Vietnamese Embassy in North Korea 
denied that a Vietnamese military delegation visited North 
Korea. According to them, the Vietnamese defense minister will 
visit Pyongyang this year as planned earlier, but they declined 
to say what is in the plan. 

</TEXT>

