<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Grachev Cited on Military Cooperation With Kuwait </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Grachev Cited on Military Cooperation With Kuwait </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3005150894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1351 GMT 30 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3005150894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vadim Byrkin] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 30 TASS -- The equipment of the Kuwaiti 
army with the newest Russian arms which have been demonstrated 
to Kuwaiti military leaders and which will soon begin arriving 
in Kuwait will help increase Kuwait's defence capability, 
Russian Defence Minister Pavel Grachev said. 
  The Russian Defence Ministry will also train specialists to 
operate and maintain Russian military equipment in Kuwait, 
Grachev said at a meeting with visiting Kuwaiti parliament 
chairman Ahmad al-Sa'dun in Moscow on Monday. 
  Kuwait is the first Persian Gulf country to have signed a 
military cooperation agreement with Russia. "Russia strictly and 
consistently observes the spirit of the agreement signed by the 
defence ministers of the two countries on November 29, 1993 in 
Moscow," Grachev said. 
  He used as an example the joint Russian-Kuwaiti military 
exercises which Russia is ready to repeat and military and 
technical cooperation between the two countries. 
  The Russian minister pointed to the similarity of positions 
of the Russian and Kuwaiti leaders on regional and global 
security, including Middle East settlement and the resolution of 
the crisis in Yemen. 
  Grachev welcomed the visit of the Kuwaiti parliamentary 
delegation to Russia as an important event in the development of 
bilateral cooperation, including in the military sphere. 
  Ahmad al-Sa'dun told journalists after the meeting that the 
aim of his visit is to convey the warmest wishes and 
gratefulness of the people of Kuwait for Russia's firm position 
on the Iraqi invasion of Kuwait in 1990. 
  He also pointed to the closeness of his views on 
Russian-Kuwaiti military cooperation with Grachev's and said 
that the Kuwaiti parliament fully supported and ratified the 
agreement on military cooperation between the two countries. He 
expressed the confidence that the Russian lawmakers will follow 
suit. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

