<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian, Ukrainian Border Regions To Cooperate </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian, Ukrainian Border Regions To Cooperate </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2705192494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1819 GMT 27 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2705192494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Anatoliy Gordeyev] </F>
  [Text] Donetsk May 27 TASS -- At their meeting in Donetsk 
today, leaders of frontier regions of Russia and Ukraine adopted 
a number of documents which will regulate economic and cultural 
cooperation between regions. 
  Representatives of the Rostov, Bryansk, Kursk, Voronezh and 
Belgorod regions of russia, and the Kharkov, Lugansk, Sumy, 
Chernigov and Donetsk regions of Ukraine have established an 
executive committee of the council of leaders of frontier 
regions and elected co-chairmen. During the first year the work 
of the executive committee will be coordinated by Vasiliy 
Ryabykh, head of the department in the administration of the 
Belgorod region. 
  One of the main documents signed by participants in the 
meeting is a package of proposals on inserting amendments in 
standard acts of the two states regulating frontier relations. 
  The status of frontier regions envisages real business 
cooperation between neighboring regions. On the basis of this 
document import and export of industrial commodities 
manufactured there and intended for the use at plants located in 
neighboring regions, must be exempted from customs duties and 
taxes. 
  Participants in the meeting also discussed the mechanism for 
the implementation of the Ukrainian president's decree "on 
measures on the development of economic cooperation among 
regions of Ukraine and frontier regions of the Russian 
Federation" which provides for the possibility for students of 
one republic to study in educational establishments of the other 
republic. It was noted at the meeting that positive experience 
in this field was accumulated, for instance, by the Rostov and 
Donetsk regions which are carrying out the exchange of students. 
  The meeting also considered a question of setting up an 
association of economic cooperation called the 
"Russian-Ukrainian Union". 
  However, participants in the meeting stressed that all these 
documents just as cooperation between separate regions of the 
contiguous states would remain only good wishes if the 
aspiration for neighborliness was not legalized by corresponding 
inter-state acts. In this connection participants in the 
meeting appealed to the presidents of Russia and Ukraine to 
speed up the working out and signing of a treaty on friendship, 
cooperation and partnership between the two states. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

