<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Calls for Revision of Border Controls With CIS </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Calls for Revision of Border Controls With CIS </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2705140994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1125 
GMT 27 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2705140994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladimir Gondusov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 27 May -- Principles of Russia's border 
policy will be set out today by Boris Yeltsin at a conference of 
top commanders of the Russian border troops. On the eve of the 
president's address the deputy commanders-in-chief of the 
Russian border troops and commanders of border districts and 
groups were presented to him. 
  On arrival at border troops headquarters, Yeltsin said he 
intended to discuss with border troops the complex tasks facing 
the defenders of the Russian border. The president spoke of the 
need to organize a new system for the protection of borders with 
the Baltic republics, the Transcaucasus, and other states of the 
CIS. 
  Yeltsin stressed that, in accordance with Russia's new 
constitution, it was necessary to improve the legislative basis 
for the activities of border forces and departments that 
cooperate with them. 

</TEXT>

