<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Crimean Security Service Affirms Loyalty to Ukraine </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Crimean Security Service Affirms Loyalty to Ukraine </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2705104394 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 0830 GMT 27 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2705104394 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sevastopol, 26 May -- The Crimean security service 
personnel have declared their support for the Ukrainian 
president's edict disbanding the service. They confirmed their 
subordination to the Ukrainian leadership and expressed their 
willingness for close cooperation with the leaders of Crimea 
"for the sake of solving vital problems in the region." The 
appeal by the personnel of the Ukrainian security service 
directorate in Crimea to the Crimean president and parliament 
was published in the Crimean press. 

</TEXT>

