<H3> <TI>   Pro-Russian National Front Formed in Crimea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Pro-Russian National Front Formed in Crimea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK2705175194 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 27 May 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> MK2705175194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Captain 1st Rank Pasyakin report in the "News from the </F>
Regions" column: "Hryvna Advancing; Coupon in Rapid Retreat"] 
  [Text] Sevastopol -- Following the deterioration in the 
situation in Crimea, a meeting took place in Sevastopol of 
representatives of various parties and movements which created 
the National Front "Sevastopol-Fleet-Russia." Crimean Supreme 
Soviet deputy Aleksandr Kruglov has been elected its chairman. 
  Political instability is leading to economic instability. 
The U.S. dollar, the West German mark, and the Russian ruble 
have surged in value. Dollar bills are being bought at the rate 
of $1 per 50,000 karbovanets. Large-denomination Russian bank 
notes (they are especially valued) go at 1:25. The people, 
repeatedly cheated by the state and "fed" by rumors about the 
introduction of the Ukrainian hryvna, are actively dumping 
coupons and sweeping everything off the shelves. 

</TEXT>

